    <title>OpenStack Compute Node for Hyper-V</title>
    <para>Nova-compute can run as a 32bit service upon Microsoft's Hyper-V Hypervisor allowing Hyper-V compute nodes within an OpenStack Cloud.</para>
    <para>Currently the following platforms are supported:</para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <title>Windows Server 2008r2</title>
                <para>Both Server and Core with the Hyper-V role enabled</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <title>Windows Server 2012</title>
                <para>Server and Core (with the Hyper-V role enabled), and Hyper-V Server</para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
    <title>Installation Requirements</title>
    <section>
        <title>Python 2.7.3</title>
        <para>Python 2.7.3 must be installed prior to installing the OpenStack Compute Driver on the Hyper-V server.  Download and then install the MSI for windows here:</para>
         <itemizedlist>
             <listitem><link xlink:href="http://www.python.org/ftp/python/2.7.3/python-2.7.3.msi" >http://www.python.org/ftp/python/2.7.3/python-2.7.3.msi</link></listitem>
             <listitem>Install the MSI accepting the default options.</listitem>
             <listitem>The installation will put python in C:/python27.</listitem>
         </itemizedlist>
    </section>
