    <section>
        <title>Local Storage Considerations</title>
        <para>Local storage on the compute node needs to have ample storage for storing the virtual machine images running on the compute nodes.   You may use a sinlge volume for all, or partition it into an OS volume and VM volume.   It is up to the individual deploying to decided.</para>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Configure NTP</title>
        <para>Network time services must be configured to ensure proper operation of the Hyper-V compute node.  To set network time on your Hyper-V host  you will need to run the following commands</para>
        <itemizedlist>
           <listitem>net stop w32time</listitem>
           <listitem>w32tm /config /manualpeerlist:pool.ntp.org,0x8 /syncfromflags:MANUAL</listitem>
           <listitem>net start w32time</listitem>
         </itemizedlist>
    </section>
